-- Pound Drops Versus Dollar After Data Confirms U.K. GDP Shrank
-- B y   M a r k   M c C o r d
-- 2013-03-27T09:39:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-27/pound-drops-versus-dollar-after-data-confirms-u-k-gdp-shrank.html
The pound reversed gains versus the
dollar after a government report confirmed U.K. gross domestic
product shrank in the fourth quarter.  Sterling dropped 0.1 percent to $1.5139 at 9:35 p.m. London
time after touching $1.5181. It pared an advance versus the euro
to trade 0.2 percent higher at 84.66 pence.  GDP fell 0.3 percent, the same as previously estimated by
the  Office for National Statistics .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mark McCord at 
 mmccord2@bloomberg.net  